TextEng: Why are the dwarves at war with you?
Text: 왜 드워프들이 너희와 전쟁을 벌이는 거야?

TextEng: Me wonders what dwarf is fighting you for.
Text: 나 궁금해 드워프 왜 너희 싸워.

TextEng: All right, dryad. Now it's your turn to die.
Text: 알았어, 드라이어드. 이제 네가 죽을 차례야.

TextEng: Me likes killing dryad. You ready to die?
Text: 나 드라이어드 죽이는 거 좋아. 너 죽을 준비됐어?

TextEng: I think I will go now. Farewell.
Me not talk no more. Me go. Bye!
Text: 나 더 얘기 안 해. 나 가. 안녕!

TextEng: What is this place? How can this world exist inside a snow globe?
Text: 여기가 어디야? 어떻게 이 세계가 스노 글로브 안에 있을 수 있어?

TextEng: What this place be? How it be inside snowball?
Text: 여기 뭐야? 어떻게 눈 내리는 공 안에 있어?

TextEng: I want to ask you some questions.
Me want ask you some questions.
Have you always been at war with the dwarves?
You always be at war with dwarves?
What do you make of this amulet?
What you think 'bout this amulet?
That's horrible!
That be bad life.
You are immortal! You get to live forever.
Text: 넌 불멸이잖아! 영원히 살 수 있어.

TextEng: You not never die. You be live forever!
Text: 너 안 죽어. 너 영원히 살아!

TextEng: Can you do anything to fix it?
You know how for fix it?
Can you make it magic?
You know how make it magic?
Are you okay? Is something wrong?
What the matter with you?
Tell me more about this vision.
Text: 그 환영에 대해 좀 더 말해줘.

TextEng: You say more 'bout this vision.
Maybe I could free you from this Master.
Text: 내가 이 주인으로부터 널 해방시켜 줄 수도 있어.

TextEng: Maybe me could free you from this Master.
Text: 나 주인한테서 너 자유롭게 해줄 수 있어.

TextEng: Immortal? What are you talking about?
Immortal? What you mean by that?
